%I A394421 #8 Apr 11 2026 23:06:26
%S A394421 1,2,6,10,8,14,12,22,20,26,24,34,32,38,36,46,44,42,40,35,25,15,21,27,
%T A394421 33,30,39,45,51,57,60,58,56,52,62,64,74,72,82,80,76,78,84,86,88,94,92,
%U A394421 90,93,96,87,81,69,66,68,70,65,55,75,95,85,100,102,104,106,108
%N A394421 a(1) = 1, a(2) = 2; for n > 2, a(n) is an unused number that is as close as possible to a(n-1), shares a factor with a(n-1), and rad(a(n)*a(n-1)) has not previously occurred as the rad value of the product of adjacent terms, where rad(k) = A007947(k). If two such numbers exist then the smaller is chosen.
%C A394421 The sequence uses a similar method to A392505 for choosing a(n) except here a(n) is chosen to be as close as possible to a(n-1), with preference given to the smaller value if two numbers exist that are the same distance from a(n-1).
%C A394421 The sequence consists of long runs of purely odd or even terms, the later runs often with terms separated by 2. These are interrupted with occasional runs of terms with very large drops in value, some of which end with primes. See the attached image. In the first 10^7 terms the only prime terms, in order of appearance, are 2, 7, 31, 53, 23, 83, 1847, 1223, 37, 127, 5531, and 2591, the last appearing at a(6547201). It is unknown if all numbers eventually appear.
%C A394421 In the same range the only fixed points are 1, 2, 235, and 1307939, although it is likely more exist.
%C A394421 See A394422 for the rad value of the product of adjacent terms.
%H A394421 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A394421/b394421.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A394421 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A394421/a394421.png">Image of the first 10^7 terms</a>. The colors are graduated across the spectrum from red to violet to show the total number of prime factors of each term, counted with multiplicity. The thin green line is a(n) = n.
%e A394421 a(5) = 8 as 8 is unused, shares a factor with a(4) = 10, rad(10*8) = 10 has not occurred previously as the rad value of the product of adjacent terms, and 8 is the closest number to a(4) = 10 that satisfies these criteria.
%Y A394421 Cf. A394422 (rad value), A007947, A392505, A386482, A064413.
